---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: 'PRP Microneedling | D-Essence Wellness',
  description:
    'Microneedling combined with platelet-rich plasma (PRP) to support collagen, refine texture, soften acne scars, and enhance tone with minimal downtime.',
  canonical: '/services/prp-microneedling/',
  type: 'website',
  jsonLd: [
    {
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@type': 'Service',
      name: 'PRP Microneedling',
      serviceType: 'Microneedling with Platelet-Rich Plasma',
      areaServed: 'New Windsor, New York',
      provider: {
        '@type': 'MedicalBusiness',
        name: 'D-Essence Wellness',
        address: {
          '@type': 'PostalAddress',
          streetAddress: '871 Blooming Grove Turnpike Suite 102',
          addressLocality: 'New Windsor',
          addressRegion: 'NY',
          postalCode: '12553',
          addressCountry: 'US'
        }
      },
      url: 'https://dessencewellness.com/services/prp-microneedling/'
    }
  ]
};
---

<BaseLayout seo={seo}>
  <!-- ===== HERO (dark) ===== -->
  <section class="bg-neutral-950 text-white">
    <div class="container pt-28 pb-10 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/60">
        <span>Services</span><span class="opacity-40">•</span><span>Advanced Skin Care</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">PRP Microneedling</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-white/80">
        Collagen induction with your own platelet-rich plasma to refine texture, soften scars and fine lines,
        and boost luminosity—while keeping downtime minimal.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-sm">
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Series</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">3–6 sessions</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Spacing</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">Every 4–6 weeks</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Areas</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">Face, neck, chest, hands</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white/5 ring-1 ring-white/10 p-3">
          <div class="text-white/70">Downtime</div>
          <div class="mt-0.5 font-medium">1–3 days redness</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CONTENT (white) ===== -->
  <section class="bg-white text-neutral-900">
    <div class="container py-12 sm:py-14">

      <!-- Overview -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Overview</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            Microneedling uses fine, controlled microchannels to prompt the skin’s repair response and support
            new collagen. When paired with platelet-rich plasma prepared from your own blood, high-value growth
            factors are delivered to freshly created channels to amplify rejuvenation, help speed recovery,
            and enhance overall results.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            Common goals include improving texture and tone, softening acne or surgical scars, reducing the
            look of enlarged pores, and restoring a more even, luminous complexion. It can be performed on the
            face and on areas like the neck, chest, and hands.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-5">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium">Key benefits</h3>
            <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Refines texture and softens fine lines
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Improves the look of acne and surgical scars
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Promotes more even tone and radiance
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Helps reduce the look of enlarged pores
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                PRP may support faster recovery vs. microneedling alone
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-neutral-500">
              Individual outcomes vary; some indications may respond better than others.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What to expect -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-5">
          <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">What to expect</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700">
            Your visit includes a full skin assessment and review of medical history. A small blood draw
            prepares PRP via centrifugation. Numbing cream is applied for comfort before the device makes
            precise, depth-controlled passes. PRP is layered over (and may be lightly infused into) the
            microchannels to optimize delivery of growth factors.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-7">
          <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">The session</div>
              <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
                <li>Topical numbing for comfort</li>
                <li>Microneedling with adjusted depth by area</li>
                <li>Immediate PRP application to treated skin</li>
                <li>Typical time: ~30–60 minutes depending on areas</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">Timeline</div>
              <ul class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-1.5">
                <li>Day 0: redness/tightness is common</li>
                <li>Days 1–3: mild swelling or flaking may occur</li>
                <li>Weeks 2–4: visible gains in tone/texture</li>
                <li>Ongoing: collagen remodeling over weeks</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5 sm:col-span-2">
              <div class="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-900">Series planning</div>
              <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral-700">
                Most plans include 3–6 sessions spaced every 4–6 weeks, with maintenance as needed. We’ll
                outline realistic goals and a routine that supports skin health between visits.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Aftercare -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Aftercare</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-700 space-y-2">
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Avoid rubbing or scrubbing for 24–48 hours; use gentle cleanser and soothing hydrators.
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Skip heavy makeup the first day; resume light, non-irritating products as advised.
              </li>
              <li class="inline-flex items-start gap-2">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M20 6L9 17l-5-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                Avoid intense exercise, steam, or sauna for 48 hours.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
              Daily SPF, smart hydration, and a simplified routine help the skin recover smoothly.
              Expect mild redness or tightness that settles within a few days. Contact the clinic if you notice
              unusual pain, spreading redness, fever, or other unexpected symptoms.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Safety & Risks -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Safety & risks</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Common, temporary effects</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Redness, mild swelling, tightness</li>
              <li>Small bruises or pinpoint bleeding</li>
              <li>Light flaking as skin renews</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <div class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Precautions & contraindications</div>
            <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1.5">
              <li>Active infection, inflamed acne, eczema flare, or open wounds</li>
              <li>Recent strong retinoids or aggressive procedures—timing matters</li>
              <li>Bleeding/platelet disorders or anticoagulants—requires evaluation</li>
              <li>History of poor healing or keloids—use caution</li>
              <li>Pregnancy or breastfeeding—typically deferred</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-neutral-500">
          Educational information only; not medical advice. Candidacy, technique, and intervals are determined by your clinician.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">FAQ</h2>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4">
          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">How many sessions will I need?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Most plans include 3–6 sessions every 4–6 weeks. Maintenance varies by goals, area, and response.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">When will I see results?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Early improvements often appear by weeks 2–4, with continued collagen remodeling over subsequent weeks.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Is it painful?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Topical numbing is used to keep you comfortable. Mild redness/tightness is expected for a day or two.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details class="group rounded-xl bg-white ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-5">
            <summary class="list-none cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium text-neutral-900">Is PRP always better than microneedling alone?</span>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path d="M5.8 7.3a1 1 0 011.4 0L10 10.1l2.8-2.8a1 1 0 111.4 1.4l-3.5 3.5a1 1 0 01-1.4 0L5.8 8.7a1 1 0 010-1.4z"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 text-sm">
              Evidence supports PRP as a helpful adjunct for many patients; results can vary by concern and skin type.
              We’ll discuss where PRP adds the most value for you.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-50 ring-1 ring-neutral-200 p-6 flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
          <div class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
            Ready to explore a plan for texture, tone, or scars? We’ll tailor a conservative series and home routine.
          </div>
          <a href="/contact-us/" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-neutral-900 text-white px-5 py-2.5 text-sm hover:bg-neutral-800 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-neutral-300">
            Contact Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
